Aspect Model Vehicles

urn:samm:io.catenax.fleet.vehicles:4.0.0#Vehicles
For Catena-X(CX) business case Quality Management. Supported technical features: delta update feature, meta information feature and additionalInformationList key-value pairs. The supported model features are described in detail in the Catena-X Quality KIT. FleetVehicles data model is used to exchange basic vehicle information - mainly how the vehicle was built - with all installed equipments and engines in the car. In addition, there is built and sold date + country were the vehicle was sold to better restrict the area of the problem or to exclude regional areas from the problem.

Constraints
  • Date Regular Expression Nullable
    Description
    This regular expressions enforces a given date according ISO 8601 local date. General format is YYYY-MM-DD. YYYY can be 0000..9999. MM-DD is checked together: months 01,03,05,07,08,10,12 must have DD in the range of 01..31 days, months 04,06,09,11 must have DD in the range of 01..30 days, month 02 must have DD in the range of 01..29 days.
    Regular expression
    ^([0-9]{4})-(((0[1,3,5,7,8]|1[0,2])-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(3[0,1])))|((0[4,6,9]|11)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(30)))|((02)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9]))))$|^null$|^NULL$

    ^([0-9]{4})-(((0[1,3,5,7,8]|1[0,2])-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(3[0,1])))|((0[4,6,9]|11)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(30)))|((02)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9]))))$|^null$|^NULL$

Characteristic

Example

No
In payload
Yes
Payload key
soldDate
Constraints
  • Date Regular Expression Nullable
    Description
    This regular expressions enforces a given date according ISO 8601 local date. General format is YYYY-MM-DD. YYYY can be 0000..9999. MM-DD is checked together: months 01,03,05,07,08,10,12 must have DD in the range of 01..31 days, months 04,06,09,11 must have DD in the range of 01..30 days, month 02 must have DD in the range of 01..29 days.
    Regular expression
    ^([0-9]{4})-(((0[1,3,5,7,8]|1[0,2])-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(3[0,1])))|((0[4,6,9]|11)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(30)))|((02)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9]))))$|^null$|^NULL$

    Description
    The provided regular expression ensures that the UUID is composed of five groups of characters separated by hyphens, in the form 8-4-4-4-12 for a total of 36 characters (32 hexadecimal characters and 4 hyphens), optionally prefixed by "urn:uuid:" to make it an IRI.

Record status
The record operation enumeration can be used to realize delta update concept. An example using scenario that data delivery runs weekly: Week0: All data is transferred -> all rows have recordStatus=new. Week1: Only the changed data is transferred: That means new rows, or updated or deleted rows: New rows get recordStatus=new, changed rows get recordStatus=changed and deleted/removed rows get recordStatus=deleted.
Name
recordStatus
Characteristic
Enumeration
Values
  • new
  • updated
  • deleted
  • same
Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string
Example
updated
Optional
Yes
In payload
Yes
Payload key
recordStatus
